            <t:div type="edition" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="etiopica">
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="30" xml:id="chapter30Eth">
                    <t:ab>ወእንዘ፡ ያንጐርጐሩ፡ ብዙኃን፡ በእንተ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                     <t:lem wit="#Σ">ዘኢይባቍዕ፡</t:lem>
                        <t:note>
                        <t:foreign xml:lang="la">fortasse in</t:foreign> ዘኢይበቍዕ፡ <t:foreign xml:lang="la">emendandum</t:foreign>
                     </t:note>
                        </t:app> 
                        ሢመ<t:app>
                     <t:lem wit="#Σ">
                        <t:choice>
                           <t:corr resp="AB">ት፡</t:corr>
                           <t:sic>ተ፡</t:sic>
                        </t:choice>
                     </t:lem>
                  </t:app> 
                        ቦእለ፡ ሮጹ፡ <t:app>
                     <t:lem wit="#Σ">
                        <t:choice>
                           <t:orig>ሰብእ፡</t:orig>
                           <t:reg>ሰብአ፡</t:reg>
                        </t:choice>
                     </t:lem>
                  </t:app> 
                        ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ እለ፡ አለክስንድርያ፡ ወነገ ርዎሙ፡ ለኤጲስቆጶሳት፡ በቤተ፡ ሞቅሕ፡ ድፍረቶ፡ ለሜሊጢስ። ወሰሚ ዖሙ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                     <t:lem wit="#Σ">አፈድ<t:choice>
                           <t:corr resp="AB">ፈ</t:corr>
                           <t:sic>ፋ</t:sic>
                        </t:choice>ዱ፡</t:lem>
                  </t:app> 
                        ሐዚነ፡ በእንተ፡ እከየ፡ ትዝልፍቱ፡ ወሐሊዮሙ፡ ዘ ንተ፡ ከመ፡ ኢሀሎ፡ 
                        ለበቍዔት፡ ይብጻሕ፡ ጸሐፉ፡ ሎቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ እን ተ፡ ትብል፡ ከመዝ፡</t:ab>
                </t:div>
                
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="31" xml:id="chapter31Eth">
                    <t:label>Ep. episcop.</t:label>
                    <t:ab>
                  <t:app type="testes">
                     <t:lem>አስኪስ፡</t:lem>
                     <t:note>
                        <t:foreign xml:lang="la">inc. La</t:foreign>
                     </t:note>
                  </t:app> 
                        ወጳኩሜ፡ ወቴዎድሮስ፡ ወፈልያስ፡ ለሜሊጢስ፡ ለፍቁር፡ እ ኁነ፡ ለዘ፡ አሐዱ፡ ቅኔነ፡ በእግዚ እ፡ ፍሥሓ። </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="32" xml:id="chapter32Eth">
                    <t:ab>ቅድመ፡ እንከ፡ ነገ ረ፡ ሐሰተ፡ ወቃለ፡ <t:app>
                        <t:lem wit="#Σ">
                        <t:choice>
                           <t:corr resp="AB">ም</t:corr>
                           <t:sic>መ</t:sic>
                        </t:choice>ኑነ፡</t:lem>
                    </t:app> እን ዘ፡ 
                        ይመስለነ፡ እለ፡ እምኀቤከ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">በ<t:choice>
                           <t:orig>ጸ</t:orig>
                           <t:reg>ጽ</t:reg>
                        </t:choice>ሑ፡</t:lem>
                        </t:app>
                        ኀቤነ፡ ወዜነዉነ፡ ዘኢይ<t:pb n="8vb" corresp="#Σ"/>ደሉ፡ ለሕገ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">መለኮ<t:supplied reason="lost" resp="AB">ት፡</t:supplied>
                     </t:lem>
                        </t:app> ድፍረተ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">ለሥርዓ<t:supplied reason="lost" resp="AB">ተ፡ ቤ</t:supplied>ተ፡</t:lem>
                        </t:app> 
                        ክርስቲያን፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">ወባ<t:supplied reason="lost" resp="AB">ሕ</t:supplied>ቱ፡</t:lem>
                        </t:app> 
                        ተገብረ፡ እምኀቤከ፡ ወበእዘ ኒነ፡ ኢፈቀድነ፡ ንስምዖ፡ እንዘ፡ ን ኔጽር፡ ውስተ፡ ዕበየ፡ ድፍረት፡ ወ ውስተ፡ <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">‡ እለ፡ ይፈርሁ፡ ይሠየ ሙ። ‡</t:lem>
                            <t:note>
                        <t:foreign xml:lang="la">corruptum videtur, cf. <t:hi rendition="simple:italic">connatus incertos</t:hi> La</t:foreign>
                     </t:note>
                        </t:app>
               </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="33" xml:id="chapter33Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                        ወእስመ፡ መዜንዋን፡ በጽ ሑ፡ ኀቤነ፡ ብዙኃን፡ አጠየቅናሆ ሙ፡ በአሀይምኖ፡ ወስምዕ፡ ኮኑ፡ ዘ ተገብረ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">ወኢክ<t:choice>
                           <t:orig>ሓ</t:orig>
                           <t:reg>ሕ</t:reg>
                        </t:choice>ዱ።</t:lem>
                        </t:app> 
                        ወበእንተዝ፡ 
                        <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">አስተድሚ<t:choice>
                           <t:orig>ም</t:orig>
                           <t:reg>መ</t:reg>
                        </t:choice>ነ፡</t:lem>
                        </t:app> ግብረ፡ ረሰይነ፡ ዘን ተ፡ መጽሐፍ፡
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="34" xml:id="chapter34Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                         ንጽሐፍ፡ ኀቤከ፡ ዘ ከመ፡ እፎ፡ ነገሥጋሥ፡ ወሐዛን፡ ለ ኵልነ፡ ወለለ፡ አሐዱ፡ 
                        አሐዱ፡ ኮ ነ፡ <t:app>
                            <t:lem wit="#Σ">
                        <t:choice>
                           <t:corr resp="AB">ዘ</t:corr>
                           <t:sic>ዝ</t:sic>
                        </t:choice>ኮነ፡</t:lem>
                        </t:app> 
                        ሢመተ፡ እምኀቤከ፡ በ ደወል፡ ኀበ፡ ኢኮነ፡ ምህላዊከ፡ ወዘ እንበለ፡ ኀጣእነ፡ ወሕዳጠስ፡ እንዘ፡
                        ከመዝስ፡ ብነ፡ ለዘሊፎት፡ ወኢንት ዓቀብ።
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
            </t:div>
            
            <t:div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:id="translationEthio" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5064HEpA#etiopica">
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="30" xml:id="transchapter30Eth">
                <t:ab>While many murmured for the fact that the appointment was not
                        useful, there were people of the church of ʾAlaksǝndǝryā 
                        who run and reported to the bishops in prison the insolence of Meliṭis. 
                        Having heard, they became extremely sorrowful because of the pravity of 
                        his obstinacy and considering that this would not have resulted 
                        for usefulness, they wrote him a letter that said as follows:</t:ab>
                </t:div>
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="31" xml:id="transchapter31Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                        <t:app type="loci">
                     <t:lem>ʾAsǝkis, Ṗākume, Tewodros and Falyās</t:lem>
                            <t:note>GUAR., MartPetLat, c. 458D: <t:foreign xml:lang="la">ubi quattuor episcopi nominantur</t:foreign>
                     </t:note>
                  </t:app> 
                        to Meliṭis, our beloved brother with 
                        whom we share our service, greeting in the Lord.
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="32" xml:id="transchapter32Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                        At first since it seemed to us an account of falsehood and a neglectable word, what those 
                        who arrived from you had told us, contrary to the divine [Law], an insolence towards the rule 
                        of the Church, yet it had been committed on your part and with our ears we did 
                        not want to listen to it, looking at the enormity of the insolence and at the ‡ fearful who were being appointed; ‡
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="33" xml:id="transchapter33Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                        and since many had come to us, we ascertained their reliability and they 
                        witnessed to what had been done and they did not deny. For this reason, being surprised, we deemed it necessary
                        to write this letter to you:
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
                <t:div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="34" xml:id="transchapter34Eth">
                    <t:ab>
                        of what agitation and pain for all of us and everyone was any appointment 
                        (carried out) by you in a diocese where is not your see, although we are not 
                        able (to express it), yet being on few points, as follows, in our capacity, 
                        we will not refrain from reproaching.
                    </t:ab>
                </t:div>
